---
description: Node.js backend API rules
globs: ["apps/api/**/*.ts"]
alwaysApply: false
---

## API architecture
Route → Controller → Service → Repository (Prisma)
Never call Prisma directly from a route or controller.

## HTTP responses
- 200: success with data
- 201: resource created
- 400: validation error (Zod)
- 404: resource not found
- 500: internal error (logging required)

## Errors
Always return `{ error: string, details?: unknown }`
Never expose stack traces in HTTP responses.
